Police on Monday confirmed the body of the missing Nicola Pienaar had been found in Paarl in the backyard of a 32-year-old suspect on Sunday night. The investigation team was led to the premises by the suspect, who pointed out a secluded area in the yard, where the body was found buried under rubble, police spokesperson FC van Wyk said. https://twitter.com/search?q=nicola%20pienaar&amp;src=typd The circumstances surrounding the matter are still under investigation. More than a week ago, police arrested Jacobus Oosthuizen, 32, her boyfriend for a year, in Port Elizabeth after he was found driving the car of Pienaar s mother, Marlaine Pienaar-Vice, a psychologist. At the time, Oosthuizen told police the couple had a fight and he had dropped her off in Oudtshoorn. He appeared in the Port Elizabeth Magistrate s Court on Friday, when his case was transferred to the Paarl Magistrate s Court. The 32-year-old suspect will appear in the Paarl Magistrate s Court on Thursday on charges of theft of motor vehicle, fraud and murder, said Van Wyk.The 28-year-old Pienaar had been reported missing on January 8 by her mother. African News Agency